  "text": "The youngest age group (16 dph) corresponded to the end of the first feeding stage, where non-feeding larvae would die of starvation (Ellertsen et al. 1980) . At 30 dph, individuals were in the late larval stage, while at 37 dph, average size was close to 12 mm, corresponding to the onset of metamorphosis [CITATION_1] . By 44 dph, most of the cod had lost the larval fin fold and had visible dorsal and ventral fin structures, indicative of the early juvenile stage [CITATION_2] .",
